#: ../../../index.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Requests** is an elegant and simple HTTP library for Python, built for "
"human beings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:32
msgid "**Behold, the power of Requests**::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:34
msgid ""
">>> r = requests.get('https://api.github.com/user', auth=('user', 'pass'))\n"
">>> r.status_code\n"
"200\n"
">>> r.headers['content-type']\n"
"'application/json; charset=utf8'\n"
">>> r.encoding\n"
"'utf-8'\n"
">>> r.text\n"
"'{\"type\":\"User\"...'\n"
">>> r.json()\n"
"{'private_gists': 419, 'total_private_repos': 77, ...}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:46
msgid "See `similar code, sans Requests <https://gist.github.com/973705>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:49
msgid ""
"**Requests** allows you to send HTTP/1.1 requests extremely easily. There's "
"no need to manually add query strings to your URLs, or to form-encode your "
"POST data. Keep-alive and HTTP connection pooling are 100% automatic, thanks "
"to `urllib3 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3>`_."
msgstr ""

